91RenderStyle& RenderStyle::defaultStyle()
92{
93 static NeverDestroyed<RenderStyle> style { CreateDefaultStyle };
94 return style;
95}
96
97RenderStyle RenderStyle::create()
98{
99 return clone(defaultStyle());
100}
101
102std::unique_ptr<RenderStyle> RenderStyle::createPtr()
103{
104 return clonePtr(defaultStyle());
105}

107RenderStyle RenderStyle::clone(const RenderStyle& style)
108{
109 return RenderStyle(style, Clone);
110}
111
112std::unique_ptr<RenderStyle> RenderStyle::clonePtr(const RenderStyle& style)
113{
114 return makeUnique<RenderStyle>(style, Clone);

117RenderStyle RenderStyle::createAnonymousStyleWithDisplay(const RenderStyle& parentStyle, DisplayType display)
118{
119 auto newStyle = create();
120 newStyle.inheritFrom(parentStyle);
121 newStyle.inheritUnicodeBidiFrom(&parentStyle);
122 newStyle.setDisplay(display);
123 return newStyle;
124}

126RenderStyle RenderStyle::createStyleInheritingFromPseudoStyle(const RenderStyle& pseudoStyle)
127{
128 ASSERT(pseudoStyle.styleType() == PseudoId::Before || pseudoStyle.styleType() == PseudoId::After);
129
130 auto style = create();
131 style.inheritFrom(pseudoStyle);
132 return style;
133}

138RenderStyle::RenderStyle(CreateDefaultStyleTag)
139 : m_boxData(StyleBoxData::create())
140 , m_visualData(StyleVisualData::create())
141 , m_backgroundData(StyleBackgroundData::create())
142 , m_surroundData(StyleSurroundData::create())
143 , m_rareNonInheritedData(StyleRareNonInheritedData::create())
144 , m_rareInheritedData(StyleRareInheritedData::create())
145 , m_inheritedData(StyleInheritedData::create())
146 , m_svgStyle(SVGRenderStyle::create())
147{
148 m_inheritedFlags.emptyCells = static_cast<unsigned>(initialEmptyCells());
149 m_inheritedFlags.captionSide = static_cast<unsigned>(initialCaptionSide());
150 m_inheritedFlags.listStyleType = static_cast<unsigned>(initialListStyleType());
151 m_inheritedFlags.listStylePosition = static_cast<unsigned>(initialListStylePosition());
152 m_inheritedFlags.visibility = static_cast<unsigned>(initialVisibility());
153 m_inheritedFlags.textAlign = static_cast<unsigned>(initialTextAlign());
154 m_inheritedFlags.textTransform = static_cast<unsigned>(initialTextTransform());
155 m_inheritedFlags.textDecorations = initialTextDecoration().toRaw();
156 m_inheritedFlags.cursor = static_cast<unsigned>(initialCursor());
157#if ENABLE(CURSOR_VISIBILITY)
158 m_inheritedFlags.cursorVisibility = static_cast<unsigned>(initialCursorVisibility());
159#endif
160 m_inheritedFlags.direction = static_cast<unsigned>(initialDirection());
161 m_inheritedFlags.whiteSpace = static_cast<unsigned>(initialWhiteSpace());
162 m_inheritedFlags.borderCollapse = static_cast<unsigned>(initialBorderCollapse());
163 m_inheritedFlags.rtlOrdering = static_cast<unsigned>(initialRTLOrdering());
164 m_inheritedFlags.boxDirection = static_cast<unsigned>(initialBoxDirection());
165 m_inheritedFlags.printColorAdjust = static_cast<unsigned>(initialPrintColorAdjust());
166 m_inheritedFlags.pointerEvents = static_cast<unsigned>(initialPointerEvents());
167 m_inheritedFlags.insideLink = static_cast<unsigned>(InsideLink::NotInside);
168 m_inheritedFlags.insideDefaultButton = false;
169 m_inheritedFlags.writingMode = static_cast<unsigned>(initialWritingMode());
170#if ENABLE(TEXT_AUTOSIZING)
171 m_inheritedFlags.autosizeStatus = 0;
172#endif
173
174 m_nonInheritedFlags.effectiveDisplay = static_cast<unsigned>(initialDisplay());
175 m_nonInheritedFlags.originalDisplay = static_cast<unsigned>(initialDisplay());
176 m_nonInheritedFlags.overflowX = static_cast<unsigned>(initialOverflowX());
177 m_nonInheritedFlags.overflowY = static_cast<unsigned>(initialOverflowY());
178 m_nonInheritedFlags.verticalAlign = static_cast<unsigned>(initialVerticalAlign());
179 m_nonInheritedFlags.clear = static_cast<unsigned>(initialClear());
180 m_nonInheritedFlags.position = static_cast<unsigned>(initialPosition());
181 m_nonInheritedFlags.unicodeBidi = initialUnicodeBidi();
182 m_nonInheritedFlags.floating = static_cast<unsigned>(initialFloating());
183 m_nonInheritedFlags.tableLayout = static_cast<unsigned>(initialTableLayout());
184 m_nonInheritedFlags.hasExplicitlySetBorderRadius = false;
185 m_nonInheritedFlags.hasExplicitlySetDirection = false;
186 m_nonInheritedFlags.hasExplicitlySetWritingMode = false;
187 m_nonInheritedFlags.hasExplicitlySetTextAlign = false;
188 m_nonInheritedFlags.hasViewportUnits = false;
189 m_nonInheritedFlags.hasExplicitlyInheritedProperties = false;
190 m_nonInheritedFlags.isUnique = false;
191 m_nonInheritedFlags.emptyState = false;
192 m_nonInheritedFlags.firstChildState = false;
193 m_nonInheritedFlags.lastChildState = false;
194 m_nonInheritedFlags.isLink = false;
195 m_nonInheritedFlags.styleType = static_cast<unsigned>(PseudoId::None);
196 m_nonInheritedFlags.pseudoBits = static_cast<unsigned>(PseudoId::None);
197
198 static_assert((sizeof(InheritedFlags) <= 8), "InheritedFlags does not grow");
199 static_assert((sizeof(NonInheritedFlags) <= 8), "NonInheritedFlags does not grow");
200}

216inline RenderStyle::RenderStyle(RenderStyle& a, RenderStyle&& b)
217 : m_boxData(a.m_boxData.replace(WTFMove(b.m_boxData)))
218 , m_visualData(a.m_visualData.replace(WTFMove(b.m_visualData)))
219 , m_backgroundData(a.m_backgroundData.replace(WTFMove(b.m_backgroundData)))
220 , m_surroundData(a.m_surroundData.replace(WTFMove(b.m_surroundData)))
221 , m_rareNonInheritedData(a.m_rareNonInheritedData.replace(WTFMove(b.m_rareNonInheritedData)))
222 , m_nonInheritedFlags(std::exchange(a.m_nonInheritedFlags, b.m_nonInheritedFlags))
223 , m_rareInheritedData(a.m_rareInheritedData.replace(WTFMove(b.m_rareInheritedData)))
224 , m_inheritedData(a.m_inheritedData.replace(WTFMove(b.m_inheritedData)))
225 , m_inheritedFlags(std::exchange(a.m_inheritedFlags, b.m_inheritedFlags))
226 , m_cachedPseudoStyles(std::exchange(a.m_cachedPseudoStyles, WTFMove(b.m_cachedPseudoStyles)))
227 , m_svgStyle(a.m_svgStyle.replace(WTFMove(b.m_svgStyle)))
228{
229}

244static StyleSelfAlignmentData resolvedSelfAlignment(const StyleSelfAlignmentData& value, ItemPosition normalValueBehavior)
245{
246 if (value.position() == ItemPosition::Legacy || value.position() == ItemPosition::Normal || value.position() == ItemPosition::Auto)
247 return { normalValueBehavior, OverflowAlignment::Default };
248 return value;
249}
250
251StyleSelfAlignmentData RenderStyle::resolvedAlignItems(ItemPosition normalValueBehaviour) const
252{
253 return resolvedSelfAlignment(alignItems(), normalValueBehaviour);
254}
255
256StyleSelfAlignmentData RenderStyle::resolvedAlignSelf(const RenderStyle* parentStyle, ItemPosition normalValueBehaviour) const
257{
258 // The auto keyword computes to the parent's align-items computed value.
259 // We will return the behaviour of 'normal' value if needed, which is specific of each layout model.
260 if (!parentStyle || alignSelf().position() != ItemPosition::Auto)
261 return resolvedSelfAlignment(alignSelf(), normalValueBehaviour);
262 return parentStyle->resolvedAlignItems(normalValueBehaviour);
263}
264
265StyleSelfAlignmentData RenderStyle::resolvedJustifyItems(ItemPosition normalValueBehaviour) const
266{
267 return resolvedSelfAlignment(justifyItems(), normalValueBehaviour);
268}
269
270StyleSelfAlignmentData RenderStyle::resolvedJustifySelf(const RenderStyle* parentStyle, ItemPosition normalValueBehaviour) const
271{
272 // The auto keyword computes to the parent's justify-items computed value.
273 // We will return the behaviour of 'normal' value if needed, which is specific of each layout model.
274 if (!parentStyle || justifySelf().position() != ItemPosition::Auto)
275 return resolvedSelfAlignment(justifySelf(), normalValueBehaviour);
276 return parentStyle->resolvedJustifyItems(normalValueBehaviour);
277}

326void RenderStyle::inheritFrom(const RenderStyle& inheritParent)
327{
328 m_rareInheritedData = inheritParent.m_rareInheritedData;
329 m_inheritedData = inheritParent.m_inheritedData;
330 m_inheritedFlags = inheritParent.m_inheritedFlags;
331
332 if (m_svgStyle != inheritParent.m_svgStyle)
333 m_svgStyle.access().inheritFrom(inheritParent.m_svgStyle.get());
334}
335
336void RenderStyle::copyNonInheritedFrom(const RenderStyle& other)
337{
338 m_boxData = other.m_boxData;
339 m_visualData = other.m_visualData;
340 m_backgroundData = other.m_backgroundData;
341 m_surroundData = other.m_surroundData;
342 m_rareNonInheritedData = other.m_rareNonInheritedData;
343 m_nonInheritedFlags.copyNonInheritedFrom(other.m_nonInheritedFlags);
344
345 if (m_svgStyle != other.m_svgStyle)
346 m_svgStyle.access().copyNonInheritedFrom(other.m_svgStyle.get());
347
348 ASSERT(zoom() == initialZoom());
349}
350
351void RenderStyle::copyContentFrom(const RenderStyle& other)
352{
353 if (!other.m_rareNonInheritedData->content)
354 return;
355 m_rareNonInheritedData.access().content = other.m_rareNonInheritedData->content->clone();
356}
357
358bool RenderStyle::operator==(const RenderStyle& other) const
359{
360 // compare everything except the pseudoStyle pointer
361 return m_inheritedFlags == other.m_inheritedFlags
362 && m_nonInheritedFlags == other.m_nonInheritedFlags
363 && m_boxData == other.m_boxData
364 && m_visualData == other.m_visualData
365 && m_backgroundData == other.m_backgroundData
366 && m_surroundData == other.m_surroundData
367 && m_rareNonInheritedData == other.m_rareNonInheritedData
368 && m_rareInheritedData == other.m_rareInheritedData
369 && m_inheritedData == other.m_inheritedData
370 && m_svgStyle == other.m_svgStyle;
371}
372
373bool RenderStyle::hasUniquePseudoStyle() const
374{
375 if (!m_cachedPseudoStyles || styleType() != PseudoId::None)
376 return false;
377
378 for (auto& pseudoStyle : *m_cachedPseudoStyles) {
379 if (pseudoStyle->unique())
380 return true;
381 }
382
383 return false;
384}
385
386RenderStyle* RenderStyle::getCachedPseudoStyle(PseudoId pid) const
387{
388 if (!m_cachedPseudoStyles || !m_cachedPseudoStyles->size())
389 return nullptr;
390
391 if (styleType() != PseudoId::None)
392 return nullptr;
393
394 for (auto& pseudoStyle : *m_cachedPseudoStyles) {
395 if (pseudoStyle->styleType() == pid)
396 return pseudoStyle.get();
397 }
398
399 return nullptr;
400}
401
402RenderStyle* RenderStyle::addCachedPseudoStyle(std::unique_ptr<RenderStyle> pseudo)
403{
404 if (!pseudo)
405 return nullptr;
406
407 ASSERT(pseudo->styleType() > PseudoId::None);
408
409 RenderStyle* result = pseudo.get();
410
411 if (!m_cachedPseudoStyles)
412 m_cachedPseudoStyles = makeUnique<PseudoStyleCache>();
413
414 m_cachedPseudoStyles->append(WTFMove(pseudo));
415
416 return result;
417}
418
419void RenderStyle::removeCachedPseudoStyle(PseudoId pid)
420{
421 if (!m_cachedPseudoStyles)
422 return;
423 for (size_t i = 0; i < m_cachedPseudoStyles->size(); ++i) {
424 RenderStyle* pseudoStyle = m_cachedPseudoStyles->at(i).get();
425 if (pseudoStyle->styleType() == pid) {
426 m_cachedPseudoStyles->remove(i);
427 return;
428 }
429 }
430}

432bool RenderStyle::inheritedEqual(const RenderStyle& other) const
433{
434 return m_inheritedFlags == other.m_inheritedFlags
435 && m_inheritedData == other.m_inheritedData
436 && (m_svgStyle.ptr() == other.m_svgStyle.ptr() || m_svgStyle->inheritedEqual(other.m_svgStyle))
437 && m_rareInheritedData == other.m_rareInheritedData;
438}

440bool RenderStyle::descendantAffectingNonInheritedPropertiesEqual(const RenderStyle& other) const
441{
442 if (m_rareNonInheritedData.ptr() == other.m_rareNonInheritedData.ptr())
443 return true;
444
445 return m_rareNonInheritedData->alignItems == other.m_rareNonInheritedData->alignItems
446 && m_rareNonInheritedData->justifyItems == other.m_rareNonInheritedData->justifyItems;
447}

451static inline unsigned computeFontHash(const FontCascade& font)
452{
453 // FIXME: Would be better to hash the family name rather than hashing a hash of the family name. Also, should this use FontCascadeDescription::familyNameHash?
454 return computeHash(ASCIICaseInsensitiveHash::hash(font.fontDescription().firstFamily()), font.fontDescription().specifiedSize());
455}
456
457unsigned RenderStyle::hashForTextAutosizing() const
458{
459 // FIXME: Not a very smart hash. Could be improved upon. See <https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=121131>.
460 unsigned hash = m_rareNonInheritedData->appearance;
461 hash ^= m_rareNonInheritedData->marginBeforeCollapse;
462 hash ^= m_rareNonInheritedData->marginAfterCollapse;
463 hash ^= m_rareNonInheritedData->lineClamp.value();
464 hash ^= m_rareInheritedData->overflowWrap;
465 hash ^= m_rareInheritedData->nbspMode;
466 hash ^= m_rareInheritedData->lineBreak;
467 hash ^= WTF::FloatHash<float>::hash(m_inheritedData->specifiedLineHeight.value());
468 hash ^= computeFontHash(m_inheritedData->fontCascade);
469 hash ^= WTF::FloatHash<float>::hash(m_inheritedData->horizontalBorderSpacing);
470 hash ^= WTF::FloatHash<float>::hash(m_inheritedData->verticalBorderSpacing);
471 hash ^= m_inheritedFlags.boxDirection;
472 hash ^= m_inheritedFlags.rtlOrdering;
473 hash ^= m_nonInheritedFlags.position;
474 hash ^= m_nonInheritedFlags.floating;
475 hash ^= m_rareNonInheritedData->textOverflow;
476 hash ^= m_rareInheritedData->textSecurity;
477 return hash;
478}

480bool RenderStyle::equalForTextAutosizing(const RenderStyle& other) const
481{
482 return m_rareNonInheritedData->appearance == other.m_rareNonInheritedData->appearance
483 && m_rareNonInheritedData->marginBeforeCollapse == other.m_rareNonInheritedData->marginBeforeCollapse
484 && m_rareNonInheritedData->marginAfterCollapse == other.m_rareNonInheritedData->marginAfterCollapse
485 && m_rareNonInheritedData->lineClamp == other.m_rareNonInheritedData->lineClamp
486 && m_rareInheritedData->textSizeAdjust == other.m_rareInheritedData->textSizeAdjust
487 && m_rareInheritedData->overflowWrap == other.m_rareInheritedData->overflowWrap
488 && m_rareInheritedData->nbspMode == other.m_rareInheritedData->nbspMode
489 && m_rareInheritedData->lineBreak == other.m_rareInheritedData->lineBreak
490 && m_rareInheritedData->textSecurity == other.m_rareInheritedData->textSecurity
491 && m_inheritedData->specifiedLineHeight == other.m_inheritedData->specifiedLineHeight
492 && m_inheritedData->fontCascade.equalForTextAutoSizing(other.m_inheritedData->fontCascade)
493 && m_inheritedData->horizontalBorderSpacing == other.m_inheritedData->horizontalBorderSpacing
494 && m_inheritedData->verticalBorderSpacing == other.m_inheritedData->verticalBorderSpacing
495 && m_inheritedFlags.boxDirection == other.m_inheritedFlags.boxDirection
496 && m_inheritedFlags.rtlOrdering == other.m_inheritedFlags.rtlOrdering
497 && m_nonInheritedFlags.position == other.m_nonInheritedFlags.position
498 && m_nonInheritedFlags.floating == other.m_nonInheritedFlags.floating
499 && m_rareNonInheritedData->textOverflow == other.m_rareNonInheritedData->textOverflow;
500}

502bool RenderStyle::isIdempotentTextAutosizingCandidate(std::optional<AutosizeStatus> overrideStatus) const
503{
504 // Refer to <rdar://problem/51826266> for more information regarding how this function was generated.
505 auto fields = OptionSet<AutosizeStatus::Fields>::fromRaw(m_inheritedFlags.autosizeStatus);
506 if (overrideStatus)
507 fields = overrideStatus->fields();
508
509 if (fields.contains(AutosizeStatus::Fields::AvoidSubtree))
510 return false;
511
512 const float smallMinimumDifferenceThresholdBetweenLineHeightAndSpecifiedFontSizeForBoostingText = 5;
513 const float largeMinimumDifferenceThresholdBetweenLineHeightAndSpecifiedFontSizeForBoostingText = 25;
514
515 if (fields.contains(AutosizeStatus::Fields::FixedHeight)) {
516 if (fields.contains(AutosizeStatus::Fields::FixedWidth)) {
517 if (whiteSpace() == WhiteSpace::NoWrap) {
518 if (width().isFixed())
519 return false;
520
521 if (height().isFixed() && specifiedLineHeight().isFixed()) {
522 float specifiedSize = specifiedFontSize();
523 if (height().value() == specifiedSize && specifiedLineHeight().value() == specifiedSize)
524 return false;
525 }
526
527 return true;
528 }
529
530 if (fields.contains(AutosizeStatus::Fields::Floating)) {
531 if (specifiedLineHeight().isFixed() && height().isFixed()) {
532 float specifiedSize = specifiedFontSize();
533 if (specifiedLineHeight().value() - specifiedSize > smallMinimumDifferenceThresholdBetweenLineHeightAndSpecifiedFontSizeForBoostingText
534 && height().value() - specifiedSize > smallMinimumDifferenceThresholdBetweenLineHeightAndSpecifiedFontSizeForBoostingText) {
535 return true;
536 }
537 }
538 return false;
539 }
540
541 if (fields.contains(AutosizeStatus::Fields::OverflowXHidden))
542 return false;
543
544 return true;
545 }
546
547 if (fields.contains(AutosizeStatus::Fields::OverflowXHidden)) {
548 if (fields.contains(AutosizeStatus::Fields::Floating))
549 return false;
550
551 return true;
552 }
553
554 return true;
555 }
556
557 if (width().isFixed()) {
558 if (breakWords())
559 return true;
560
561 return false;
562 }
563
564 if (textSizeAdjust().isPercentage() && textSizeAdjust().percentage() == 100) {
565 if (fields.contains(AutosizeStatus::Fields::Floating))
566 return true;
567
568 if (fields.contains(AutosizeStatus::Fields::FixedWidth))
569 return true;
570
571 if (specifiedLineHeight().isFixed() && specifiedLineHeight().value() - specifiedFontSize() > largeMinimumDifferenceThresholdBetweenLineHeightAndSpecifiedFontSizeForBoostingText)
572 return true;
573
574 return false;
575 }
576
577 if (hasBackgroundImage() && backgroundRepeatX() == FillRepeat::NoRepeat && backgroundRepeatY() == FillRepeat::NoRepeat)
578 return false;
579
580 return true;
581}
582
583AutosizeStatus RenderStyle::autosizeStatus() const
584{
585 return OptionSet<AutosizeStatus::Fields>::fromRaw(m_inheritedFlags.autosizeStatus);
586}

595static bool positionChangeIsMovementOnly(const LengthBox& a, const LengthBox& b, const Length& width)
596{
597 // If any unit types are different, then we can't guarantee
598 // that this was just a movement.
599 if (a.left().type() != b.left().type()
600 || a.right().type() != b.right().type()
601 || a.top().type() != b.top().type()
602 || a.bottom().type() != b.bottom().type())
603 return false;
604
605 // Only one unit can be non-auto in the horizontal direction and
606 // in the vertical direction. Otherwise the adjustment of values
607 // is changing the size of the box.
608 if (!a.left().isIntrinsicOrAuto() && !a.right().isIntrinsicOrAuto())
609 return false;
610 if (!a.top().isIntrinsicOrAuto() && !a.bottom().isIntrinsicOrAuto())
611 return false;
612 // If our width is auto and left or right is specified then this
613 // is not just a movement - we need to resize to our container.
614 if ((!a.left().isIntrinsicOrAuto() || !a.right().isIntrinsicOrAuto()) && width.isIntrinsicOrAuto())
615 return false;
616
617 // One of the units is fixed or percent in both directions and stayed
618 // that way in the new style. Therefore all we are doing is moving.
619 return true;
620}

622inline bool RenderStyle::changeAffectsVisualOverflow(const RenderStyle& other) const
623{
624 if (m_rareNonInheritedData.ptr() != other.m_rareNonInheritedData.ptr()
625 && !arePointingToEqualData(m_rareNonInheritedData->boxShadow, other.m_rareNonInheritedData->boxShadow))
626 return true;
627
628 if (m_rareInheritedData.ptr() != other.m_rareInheritedData.ptr()
629 && !arePointingToEqualData(m_rareInheritedData->textShadow, other.m_rareInheritedData->textShadow))
630 return true;
631
632 if (m_inheritedFlags.textDecorations != other.m_inheritedFlags.textDecorations
633 || m_rareNonInheritedData->textDecorationStyle != other.m_rareNonInheritedData->textDecorationStyle
634 || m_rareInheritedData->textDecorationThickness != other.m_rareInheritedData->textDecorationThickness
635 || m_rareInheritedData->textUnderlineOffset != other.m_rareInheritedData->textUnderlineOffset
636 || m_rareInheritedData->textUnderlinePosition != other.m_rareInheritedData->textUnderlinePosition) {
637 // Underlines are always drawn outside of their textbox bounds when text-underline-position: under;
638 // is specified. We can take an early out here.
639 if (textUnderlinePosition() == TextUnderlinePosition::Under || other.textUnderlinePosition() == TextUnderlinePosition::Under)
640 return true;
641 return visualOverflowForDecorations(*this, nullptr) != visualOverflowForDecorations(other, nullptr);
642 }
643
644 if (hasOutlineInVisualOverflow() != other.hasOutlineInVisualOverflow())
645 return true;
646 return false;
647}

712 || first.breakAfter != second.breakAfter
713 || first.breakInside != second.breakInside)

718 // We need to make sure SimplifiedLayout can operate correctly on RenderInlines (we will need
719 // to add a selfNeedsSimplifiedLayout bit in order to not get confused and taint every line).

741 || first.aspectRatioWidth != second.aspectRatioWidth
742 || first.aspectRatioHeight != second.aspectRatioHeight) {

744 }

812bool RenderStyle::changeRequiresLayout(const RenderStyle& other, OptionSet<StyleDifferenceContextSensitiveProperty>& changedContextSensitiveProperties) const
813{
814 if (m_boxData.ptr() != other.m_boxData.ptr()) {
815 if (m_boxData->width() != other.m_boxData->width()
816 || m_boxData->minWidth() != other.m_boxData->minWidth()
817 || m_boxData->maxWidth() != other.m_boxData->maxWidth()
818 || m_boxData->height() != other.m_boxData->height()
819 || m_boxData->minHeight() != other.m_boxData->minHeight()
820 || m_boxData->maxHeight() != other.m_boxData->maxHeight())
821 return true;
822
823 if (m_boxData->verticalAlign() != other.m_boxData->verticalAlign())
824 return true;
825
826 if (m_boxData->boxSizing() != other.m_boxData->boxSizing())
827 return true;
828
829 if (m_boxData->hasAutoUsedZIndex() != other.m_boxData->hasAutoUsedZIndex())
830 return true;
831 }
832
833 if (m_surroundData->margin != other.m_surroundData->margin)
834 return true;
835
836 if (m_surroundData->padding != other.m_surroundData->padding)
837 return true;
838
839 // FIXME: We should add an optimized form of layout that just recomputes visual overflow.
840 if (changeAffectsVisualOverflow(other))
841 return true;
842
843 if (m_rareNonInheritedData.ptr() != other.m_rareNonInheritedData.ptr()
844 && rareNonInheritedDataChangeRequiresLayout(*m_rareNonInheritedData, *other.m_rareNonInheritedData, changedContextSensitiveProperties))
845 return true;
846
847 if (m_rareInheritedData.ptr() != other.m_rareInheritedData.ptr()
848 && rareInheritedDataChangeRequiresLayout(*m_rareInheritedData, *other.m_rareInheritedData))
849 return true;
850
851 if (m_inheritedData.ptr() != other.m_inheritedData.ptr()) {
852 if (m_inheritedData->lineHeight != other.m_inheritedData->lineHeight
853#if ENABLE(TEXT_AUTOSIZING)
854 || m_inheritedData->specifiedLineHeight != other.m_inheritedData->specifiedLineHeight
855#endif
856 || m_inheritedData->fontCascade != other.m_inheritedData->fontCascade
857 || m_inheritedData->horizontalBorderSpacing != other.m_inheritedData->horizontalBorderSpacing
858 || m_inheritedData->verticalBorderSpacing != other.m_inheritedData->verticalBorderSpacing)
859 return true;
860 }
861
862 if (m_inheritedFlags.boxDirection != other.m_inheritedFlags.boxDirection
863 || m_inheritedFlags.rtlOrdering != other.m_inheritedFlags.rtlOrdering
864 || m_nonInheritedFlags.position != other.m_nonInheritedFlags.position
865 || m_nonInheritedFlags.floating != other.m_nonInheritedFlags.floating
866 || m_nonInheritedFlags.originalDisplay != other.m_nonInheritedFlags.originalDisplay
867 || m_nonInheritedFlags.verticalAlign != other.m_nonInheritedFlags.verticalAlign)
868 return true;
869
870 if (static_cast<DisplayType>(m_nonInheritedFlags.effectiveDisplay) >= DisplayType::Table) {
871 if (m_inheritedFlags.borderCollapse != other.m_inheritedFlags.borderCollapse
872 || m_inheritedFlags.emptyCells != other.m_inheritedFlags.emptyCells
873 || m_inheritedFlags.captionSide != other.m_inheritedFlags.captionSide
874 || m_nonInheritedFlags.tableLayout != other.m_nonInheritedFlags.tableLayout)
875 return true;
876
877 // In the collapsing border model, 'hidden' suppresses other borders, while 'none'
878 // does not, so these style differences can be width differences.
879 if (m_inheritedFlags.borderCollapse
880 && ((borderTopStyle() == BorderStyle::Hidden && other.borderTopStyle() == BorderStyle::None)
881 || (borderTopStyle() == BorderStyle::None && other.borderTopStyle() == BorderStyle::Hidden)
882 || (borderBottomStyle() == BorderStyle::Hidden && other.borderBottomStyle() == BorderStyle::None)
883 || (borderBottomStyle() == BorderStyle::None && other.borderBottomStyle() == BorderStyle::Hidden)
884 || (borderLeftStyle() == BorderStyle::Hidden && other.borderLeftStyle() == BorderStyle::None)
885 || (borderLeftStyle() == BorderStyle::None && other.borderLeftStyle() == BorderStyle::Hidden)
886 || (borderRightStyle() == BorderStyle::Hidden && other.borderRightStyle() == BorderStyle::None)
887 || (borderRightStyle() == BorderStyle::None && other.borderRightStyle() == BorderStyle::Hidden)))
888 return true;
889 }
890
891 if (static_cast<DisplayType>(m_nonInheritedFlags.effectiveDisplay) == DisplayType::ListItem) {
892 if (m_inheritedFlags.listStyleType != other.m_inheritedFlags.listStyleType
893 || m_inheritedFlags.listStylePosition != other.m_inheritedFlags.listStylePosition)
894 return true;
895 }
896
897 if (m_inheritedFlags.textAlign != other.m_inheritedFlags.textAlign
898 || m_inheritedFlags.textTransform != other.m_inheritedFlags.textTransform
899 || m_inheritedFlags.direction != other.m_inheritedFlags.direction
900 || m_inheritedFlags.whiteSpace != other.m_inheritedFlags.whiteSpace
901 || m_nonInheritedFlags.clear != other.m_nonInheritedFlags.clear
902 || m_nonInheritedFlags.unicodeBidi != other.m_nonInheritedFlags.unicodeBidi)
903 return true;
904
905 // Check block flow direction.
906 if (m_inheritedFlags.writingMode != other.m_inheritedFlags.writingMode)
907 return true;
908
909 // Overflow returns a layout hint.
910 if (m_nonInheritedFlags.overflowX != other.m_nonInheritedFlags.overflowX
911 || m_nonInheritedFlags.overflowY != other.m_nonInheritedFlags.overflowY)
912 return true;
913
914 // If our border widths change, then we need to layout. Other changes to borders
915 // only necessitate a repaint.
916 if (borderLeftWidth() != other.borderLeftWidth()
917 || borderTopWidth() != other.borderTopWidth()
918 || borderBottomWidth() != other.borderBottomWidth()
919 || borderRightWidth() != other.borderRightWidth())
920 return true;
921
922 // If the counter directives change, trigger a relayout to re-calculate counter values and rebuild the counter node tree.
923 if (!arePointingToEqualData(m_rareNonInheritedData->counterDirectives, other.m_rareNonInheritedData->counterDirectives))
924 return true;
925
926 if ((visibility() == Visibility::Collapse) != (other.visibility() == Visibility::Collapse))
927 return true;
928
929 if (position() != PositionType::Static) {
930 if (m_surroundData->offset != other.m_surroundData->offset) {
931 // FIXME: We would like to use SimplifiedLayout for relative positioning, but we can't quite do that yet.
932 // We need to make sure SimplifiedLayout can operate correctly on RenderInlines (we will need
933 // to add a selfNeedsSimplifiedLayout bit in order to not get confused and taint every line).
934 if (position() != PositionType::Absolute)
935 return true;
936
937 // Optimize for the case where a positioned layer is moving but not changing size.
938 if (!positionChangeIsMovementOnly(m_surroundData->offset, other.m_surroundData->offset, m_boxData->width()))
939 return true;
940 }
941 }
942
943 bool hasFirstLineStyle = hasPseudoStyle(PseudoId::FirstLine);
944 if (hasFirstLineStyle != other.hasPseudoStyle(PseudoId::FirstLine))
945 return true;
946 if (hasFirstLineStyle) {
947 auto* firstLineStyle = getCachedPseudoStyle(PseudoId::FirstLine);
948 if (!firstLineStyle)
949 return true;
950 auto* otherFirstLineStyle = other.getCachedPseudoStyle(PseudoId::FirstLine);
951 if (!otherFirstLineStyle)
952 return true;
953 // FIXME: Not all first line style changes actually need layout.
954 if (*firstLineStyle != *otherFirstLineStyle)
955 return true;
956 }
957
958 if (scrollPadding() != other.scrollPadding() || scrollSnapType() != other.scrollSnapType())
959 return true;
960
961 return false;
962}
963
964bool RenderStyle::changeRequiresPositionedLayoutOnly(const RenderStyle& other, OptionSet<StyleDifferenceContextSensitiveProperty>&) const
965{
966 if (position() == PositionType::Static)
967 return false;
968
969 if (m_surroundData->offset != other.m_surroundData->offset) {
970 // Optimize for the case where a positioned layer is moving but not changing size.
971 if (position() == PositionType::Absolute && positionChangeIsMovementOnly(m_surroundData->offset, other.m_surroundData->offset, m_boxData->width()))
972 return true;
973 }
974
975 return false;
976}

1072#if ENABLE(CSS_PAINTING_API)
1073void RenderStyle::addCustomPaintWatchProperty(const String& name)
1074{
1075 auto& data = m_rareNonInheritedData.access();
1076 if (!data.customPaintWatchedProperties)
1077 data.customPaintWatchedProperties = makeUnique<HashSet<String>>();
1078 data.customPaintWatchedProperties->add(name);

1080
1081inline static bool changedCustomPaintWatchedProperty(const RenderStyle& a, const StyleRareNonInheritedData& aData, const RenderStyle& b, const StyleRareNonInheritedData& bData)
1082{
1083 auto* propertiesA = aData.customPaintWatchedProperties.get();
1084 auto* propertiesB = bData.customPaintWatchedProperties.get();
1085
1086 if (UNLIKELY(propertiesA || propertiesB)) {
1087 // FIXME: We should not need to use ComputedStyleExtractor here.
1088 ComputedStyleExtractor extractor((Element*) nullptr);
1089
1090 for (auto* watchPropertiesMap : { propertiesA, propertiesB }) {
1091 if (!watchPropertiesMap)
1092 continue;
1093
1094 for (auto& name : *watchPropertiesMap) {
1095 RefPtr<CSSValue> valueA;
1096 RefPtr<CSSValue> valueB;
1097 if (isCustomPropertyName(name)) {
1098 if (a.getCustomProperty(name))
1099 valueA = CSSCustomPropertyValue::create(*a.getCustomProperty(name));
1100 if (b.getCustomProperty(name))
1101 valueB = CSSCustomPropertyValue::create(*b.getCustomProperty(name));
1102 } else {
1103 CSSPropertyID propertyID = cssPropertyID(name);
1104 if (!propertyID)
1105 continue;
1106 valueA = extractor.valueForPropertyInStyle(a, propertyID);
1107 valueB = extractor.valueForPropertyInStyle(b, propertyID);
1108 }
1109
1110 if ((valueA && !valueB) || (!valueA && valueB))
1111 return true;
1112
1113 if (!valueA)
1114 continue;
1115
1116 if (!(*valueA == *valueB))
1117 return true;
1118 }
1119 }
1120 }
1121
1122 return false;
1123}
1124#endif

1127{
1128 if (!requiresPainting(*this) && !requiresPainting(other))
1129 return false;
1130
1131 bool currentColorDiffers = m_inheritedData->color != other.m_inheritedData->color;
1132
1133 if (m_inheritedFlags.visibility != other.m_inheritedFlags.visibility
1134 || m_inheritedFlags.printColorAdjust != other.m_inheritedFlags.printColorAdjust
1135 || m_inheritedFlags.insideLink != other.m_inheritedFlags.insideLink
1136 || m_inheritedFlags.insideDefaultButton != other.m_inheritedFlags.insideDefaultButton
1137 || m_surroundData->border != other.m_surroundData->border
1138 || !m_backgroundData->isEquivalentForPainting(*other.m_backgroundData, currentColorDiffers))
1139 return true;
1140
1141 if (m_rareNonInheritedData.ptr() != other.m_rareNonInheritedData.ptr()
1142 && rareNonInheritedDataChangeRequiresRepaint(*m_rareNonInheritedData, *other.m_rareNonInheritedData, changedContextSensitiveProperties))
1143 return true;
1144
1145 if (m_rareInheritedData.ptr() != other.m_rareInheritedData.ptr()
1146 && rareInheritedDataChangeRequiresRepaint(*m_rareInheritedData, *other.m_rareInheritedData))
1147 return true;
1148
1149#if ENABLE(CSS_PAINTING_API)
1150 if (changedCustomPaintWatchedProperty(*this, *m_rareNonInheritedData, other, *other.m_rareNonInheritedData))
1151 return true;
1152#endif
1153
1154 return false;
1155}

1157bool RenderStyle::changeRequiresRepaintIfTextOrBorderOrOutline(const RenderStyle& other, OptionSet<StyleDifferenceContextSensitiveProperty>&) const
1158{
1159 if (m_inheritedData->color != other.m_inheritedData->color
1160 || m_inheritedFlags.textDecorations != other.m_inheritedFlags.textDecorations
1161 || m_visualData->textDecoration != other.m_visualData->textDecoration
1162 || m_rareNonInheritedData->textDecorationStyle != other.m_rareNonInheritedData->textDecorationStyle
1163 || m_rareNonInheritedData->textDecorationColor != other.m_rareNonInheritedData->textDecorationColor
1164 || m_rareInheritedData->textDecorationSkip != other.m_rareInheritedData->textDecorationSkip
1165 || m_rareInheritedData->textFillColor != other.m_rareInheritedData->textFillColor
1166 || m_rareInheritedData->textStrokeColor != other.m_rareInheritedData->textStrokeColor
1167 || m_rareInheritedData->textEmphasisColor != other.m_rareInheritedData->textEmphasisColor
1168 || m_rareInheritedData->textEmphasisFill != other.m_rareInheritedData->textEmphasisFill
1169 || m_rareInheritedData->strokeColor != other.m_rareInheritedData->strokeColor
1170 || m_rareInheritedData->caretColor != other.m_rareInheritedData->caretColor)
1171 return true;
1172
1173 return false;
1174}
1175
1176bool RenderStyle::changeRequiresRecompositeLayer(const RenderStyle& other, OptionSet<StyleDifferenceContextSensitiveProperty>&) const
1177{
1178 if (m_inheritedFlags.pointerEvents != other.m_inheritedFlags.pointerEvents)
1179 return true;
1180
1181 if (m_rareNonInheritedData.ptr() != other.m_rareNonInheritedData.ptr()) {
1182 if (m_rareNonInheritedData->transformStyle3D != other.m_rareNonInheritedData->transformStyle3D
1183 || m_rareNonInheritedData->backfaceVisibility != other.m_rareNonInheritedData->backfaceVisibility
1184 || m_rareNonInheritedData->perspective != other.m_rareNonInheritedData->perspective
1185 || m_rareNonInheritedData->perspectiveOriginX != other.m_rareNonInheritedData->perspectiveOriginX
1186 || m_rareNonInheritedData->perspectiveOriginY != other.m_rareNonInheritedData->perspectiveOriginY)
1187 return true;
1188 }
1189
1190 return false;
1191}
1192
1193StyleDifference RenderStyle::diff(const RenderStyle& other, OptionSet<StyleDifferenceContextSensitiveProperty>& changedContextSensitiveProperties) const
1194{
1195 changedContextSensitiveProperties = OptionSet<StyleDifferenceContextSensitiveProperty>();
1196
1197 StyleDifference svgChange = StyleDifference::Equal;
1198 if (m_svgStyle != other.m_svgStyle) {
1199 svgChange = m_svgStyle->diff(other.m_svgStyle.get());
1200 if (svgChange == StyleDifference::Layout)
1201 return svgChange;
1202 }
1203
1204 if (changeRequiresLayout(other, changedContextSensitiveProperties))
1205 return StyleDifference::Layout;
1206
1207 // SVGRenderStyle::diff() might have returned StyleDifference::Repaint, eg. if fill changes.
1208 // If eg. the font-size changed at the same time, we're not allowed to return StyleDifference::Repaint,
1209 // but have to return StyleDifference::Layout, that's why this if branch comes after all branches
1210 // that are relevant for SVG and might return StyleDifference::Layout.
1211 if (svgChange != StyleDifference::Equal)
1212 return svgChange;
1213
1214 if (changeRequiresPositionedLayoutOnly(other, changedContextSensitiveProperties))
1215 return StyleDifference::LayoutPositionedMovementOnly;
1216
1217 if (changeRequiresLayerRepaint(other, changedContextSensitiveProperties))
1218 return StyleDifference::RepaintLayer;
1219
1220 if (changeRequiresRepaint(other, changedContextSensitiveProperties))
1221 return StyleDifference::Repaint;
1222
1223 if (changeRequiresRepaintIfTextOrBorderOrOutline(other, changedContextSensitiveProperties))
1224 return StyleDifference::RepaintIfTextOrBorderOrOutline;
1225
1226 // FIXME: RecompositeLayer should also behave as a priority bit (e.g when the style change requires layout, we know that
1227 // the content also needs repaint and it will eventually get repainted,
1228 // but a repaint type of change (e.g. color change) does not necessarily trigger recomposition).
1229 if (changeRequiresRecompositeLayer(other, changedContextSensitiveProperties))
1230 return StyleDifference::RecompositeLayer;
1231
1232 // Cursors are not checked, since they will be set appropriately in response to mouse events,
1233 // so they don't need to cause any repaint or layout.
1234
1235 // Animations don't need to be checked either. We always set the new style on the RenderObject, so we will get a chance to fire off
1236 // the resulting transition properly.
1237 return StyleDifference::Equal;
1238}
1239
1240bool RenderStyle::diffRequiresLayerRepaint(const RenderStyle& style, bool isComposited) const
1241{
1242 OptionSet<StyleDifferenceContextSensitiveProperty> changedContextSensitiveProperties;
1243
1244 if (changeRequiresRepaint(style, changedContextSensitiveProperties))
1245 return true;
1246
1247 if (isComposited && changeRequiresLayerRepaint(style, changedContextSensitiveProperties))
1248 return changedContextSensitiveProperties.contains(StyleDifferenceContextSensitiveProperty::ClipRect);
1249
1250 return false;
1251}

1397
1398void RenderStyle::applyTransform(TransformationMatrix& transform, const FloatRect& boundingBox, OptionSet<RenderStyle::TransformOperationOption> options) const
1399{
1400 // https://www.w3.org/TR/css-transforms-2/#ctm
1401 // The transformation matrix is computed from the transform, transform-origin, translate, rotate, scale, and offset properties as follows:
1402 // 1. Start with the identity matrix.
1403
1404 auto& transformOperations = m_rareNonInheritedData->transform->operations;
1405 bool applyTransformOrigin = options.contains(RenderStyle::TransformOperationOption::TransformOrigin) && ((m_rareNonInheritedData->rotate && !m_rareNonInheritedData->rotate->isIdentity()) || (m_rareNonInheritedData->scale && !m_rareNonInheritedData->scale->isIdentity()) || transformOperations.affectedByTransformOrigin());
1406
1407 // 2. Translate by the computed X, Y, and Z values of transform-origin.
1408 FloatPoint3D originTranslate;
1409 if (applyTransformOrigin) {
1410 originTranslate.setXY(boundingBox.location() + floatPointForLengthPoint(transformOriginXY(), boundingBox.size()));
1411 originTranslate.setZ(transformOriginZ());
1412 transform.translate3d(originTranslate.x(), originTranslate.y(), originTranslate.z());
1413 }
1414
1415 // 3. Translate by the computed X, Y, and Z values of translate.
1416 if (options.contains(RenderStyle::TransformOperationOption::Translate)) {
1417 if (TransformOperation* translate = m_rareNonInheritedData->translate.get())
1418 translate->apply(transform, boundingBox.size());
1419 }
1420
1421 // 4. Rotate by the computed <angle> about the specified axis of rotate.
1422 if (options.contains(RenderStyle::TransformOperationOption::Rotate)) {
1423 if (TransformOperation* rotate = m_rareNonInheritedData->rotate.get())
1424 rotate->apply(transform, boundingBox.size());
1425 }
1426
1427 // 5. Scale by the computed X, Y, and Z values of scale.
1428 if (options.contains(RenderStyle::TransformOperationOption::Scale)) {
1429 if (TransformOperation* scale = m_rareNonInheritedData->scale.get())
1430 scale->apply(transform, boundingBox.size());
1431 }
1432
1433 // 6. Translate and rotate by the transform specified by offset. (FIXME: we don't support the offset property)
1434
1435 // 7. Multiply by each of the transform functions in transform from left to right.
1436 for (auto& operation : transformOperations.operations())
1437 operation->apply(transform, boundingBox.size());
1438
1439 // 8. Translate by the negated computed X, Y and Z values of transform-origin.
1440 if (applyTransformOrigin)
1441 transform.translate3d(-originTranslate.x(), -originTranslate.y(), -originTranslate.z());
1442}

1444void RenderStyle::setPageScaleTransform(float scale)

1446 if (scale == 1)

1448 TransformOperations transform;

1453}

1542RoundedRect RenderStyle::getRoundedBorderFor(const LayoutRect& borderRect, bool includeLogicalLeftEdge, bool includeLogicalRightEdge) const
1543{
1544 RoundedRect roundedRect(borderRect);
1545 if (hasBorderRadius()) {
1546 RoundedRect::Radii radii = calcRadiiFor(m_surroundData->border, borderRect.size());
1547 radii.scale(calcBorderRadiiConstraintScaleFor(borderRect, radii));
1548 roundedRect.includeLogicalEdges(radii, isHorizontalWritingMode(), includeLogicalLeftEdge, includeLogicalRightEdge);
1549 }
1550 return roundedRect;
1551}
1552
1553RoundedRect RenderStyle::getRoundedInnerBorderFor(const LayoutRect& borderRect, bool includeLogicalLeftEdge, bool includeLogicalRightEdge) const
1554{
1555 bool horizontal = isHorizontalWritingMode();
1556 LayoutUnit leftWidth { (!horizontal || includeLogicalLeftEdge) ? borderLeftWidth() : 0 };
1557 LayoutUnit rightWidth { (!horizontal || includeLogicalRightEdge) ? borderRightWidth() : 0 };
1558 LayoutUnit topWidth { (horizontal || includeLogicalLeftEdge) ? borderTopWidth() : 0 };
1559 LayoutUnit bottomWidth { (horizontal || includeLogicalRightEdge) ? borderBottomWidth() : 0 };
1560 return getRoundedInnerBorderFor(borderRect, topWidth, bottomWidth, leftWidth, rightWidth, includeLogicalLeftEdge, includeLogicalRightEdge);
1561}
1562
1563RoundedRect RenderStyle::getRoundedInnerBorderFor(const LayoutRect& borderRect, LayoutUnit topWidth, LayoutUnit bottomWidth,
1564 LayoutUnit leftWidth, LayoutUnit rightWidth, bool includeLogicalLeftEdge, bool includeLogicalRightEdge) const
1565{
1566 auto width = std::max(0_lu, borderRect.width() - leftWidth - rightWidth);
1567 auto height = std::max(0_lu, borderRect.height() - topWidth - bottomWidth);
1568 auto roundedRect = RoundedRect {
1569 borderRect.x() + leftWidth,
1570 borderRect.y() + topWidth,
1571 width,
1572 height
1573 };
1574 if (hasBorderRadius()) {
1575 auto radii = getRoundedBorderFor(borderRect).radii();
1576 radii.shrink(topWidth, bottomWidth, leftWidth, rightWidth);
1577 roundedRect.includeLogicalEdges(radii, isHorizontalWritingMode(), includeLogicalLeftEdge, includeLogicalRightEdge);
1578 }
1579 return roundedRect;
1580}

1623const AtomString& RenderStyle::textEmphasisMarkString() const
1624{
1625 switch (textEmphasisMark()) {
1626 case TextEmphasisMark::None:
1627 return nullAtom();
1628 case TextEmphasisMark::Custom:
1629 return textEmphasisCustomMark();
1630 case TextEmphasisMark::Dot: {
1631 static MainThreadNeverDestroyed<const AtomString> filledDotString(&bullet, 1);
1632 static MainThreadNeverDestroyed<const AtomString> openDotString(&whiteBullet, 1);
1633 return textEmphasisFill() == TextEmphasisFill::Filled ? filledDotString : openDotString;
1634 }
1635 case TextEmphasisMark::Circle: {
1636 static MainThreadNeverDestroyed<const AtomString> filledCircleString(&blackCircle, 1);
1637 static MainThreadNeverDestroyed<const AtomString> openCircleString(&whiteCircle, 1);
1638 return textEmphasisFill() == TextEmphasisFill::Filled ? filledCircleString : openCircleString;
1639 }
1640 case TextEmphasisMark::DoubleCircle: {
1641 static MainThreadNeverDestroyed<const AtomString> filledDoubleCircleString(&fisheye, 1);
1642 static MainThreadNeverDestroyed<const AtomString> openDoubleCircleString(&bullseye, 1);
1643 return textEmphasisFill() == TextEmphasisFill::Filled ? filledDoubleCircleString : openDoubleCircleString;
1644 }
1645 case TextEmphasisMark::Triangle: {
1646 static MainThreadNeverDestroyed<const AtomString> filledTriangleString(&blackUpPointingTriangle, 1);
1647 static MainThreadNeverDestroyed<const AtomString> openTriangleString(&whiteUpPointingTriangle, 1);
1648 return textEmphasisFill() == TextEmphasisFill::Filled ? filledTriangleString : openTriangleString;
1649 }
1650 case TextEmphasisMark::Sesame: {
1651 static MainThreadNeverDestroyed<const AtomString> filledSesameString(&sesameDot, 1);
1652 static MainThreadNeverDestroyed<const AtomString> openSesameString(&whiteSesameDot, 1);
1653 return textEmphasisFill() == TextEmphasisFill::Filled ? filledSesameString : openSesameString;
1654 }
1655 case TextEmphasisMark::Auto:
1656 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
1657 return nullAtom();
1658 }
1659
1660 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
1661 return nullAtom();
1662}
1663
1664void RenderStyle::adjustAnimations()
1665{
1666 auto* animationList = m_rareNonInheritedData->animations.get();
1667 if (!animationList)
1668 return;
1669
1670 // Get rid of empty animations and anything beyond them
1671 for (size_t i = 0, size = animationList->size(); i < size; ++i) {
1672 if (animationList->animation(i).isEmpty()) {
1673 animationList->resize(i);
1674 break;
1675 }
1676 }
1677
1678 if (animationList->isEmpty()) {
1679 clearAnimations();
1680 return;
1681 }
1682
1683 // Repeat patterns into layers that don't have some properties set.
1684 animationList->fillUnsetProperties();
1685}
1686
1687void RenderStyle::adjustTransitions()
1688{
1689 auto* transitionList = m_rareNonInheritedData->transitions.get();
1690 if (!transitionList)
1691 return;
1692
1693 // Get rid of empty transitions and anything beyond them
1694 for (size_t i = 0, size = transitionList->size(); i < size; ++i) {
1695 if (transitionList->animation(i).isEmpty()) {
1696 transitionList->resize(i);
1697 break;
1698 }
1699 }
1700
1701 if (transitionList->isEmpty()) {
1702 clearTransitions();
1703 return;
1704 }
1705
1706 // Repeat patterns into layers that don't have some properties set.
1707 transitionList->fillUnsetProperties();
1708
1709 // Make sure there are no duplicate properties.
1710 // This is an O(n^2) algorithm but the lists tend to be short, so it is probably OK.
1711 for (size_t i = 0; i < transitionList->size(); ++i) {
1712 for (size_t j = i + 1; j < transitionList->size(); ++j) {
1713 if (transitionList->animation(i).property().id == transitionList->animation(j).property().id) {
1714 // toss i
1715 transitionList->remove(i);
1716 j = i;
1717 }
1718 }
1719 }
1720}

1736const Animation* RenderStyle::transitionForProperty(CSSPropertyID property) const
1737{
1738 auto* transitions = this->transitions();
1739 if (!transitions)
1740 return nullptr;
1741 for (size_t i = 0, size = transitions->size(); i < size; ++i) {
1742 auto& animation = transitions->animation(i);
1743 if (animation.property().mode == Animation::TransitionMode::All || animation.property().id == property)
1744 return &animation;
1745 }
1746 return nullptr;
1747}

1831int RenderStyle::computeLineHeight(const Length& lineHeightLength) const
1832{
1833 // Negative value means the line height is not set. Use the font's built-in spacing.
1834 if (lineHeightLength.isNegative())
1835 return fontMetrics().lineSpacing();
1836
1837 if (lineHeightLength.isPercentOrCalculated())
1838 return minimumValueForLength(lineHeightLength, computedFontPixelSize());
1839
1840 return clampTo<int>(lineHeightLength.value());
1841}

1843void RenderStyle::setWordSpacing(Length&& value)
1844{
1845 float fontWordSpacing;
1846 switch (value.type()) {
1847 case LengthType::Auto:
1848 fontWordSpacing = 0;
1849 break;
1850 case LengthType::Percent:
1851 fontWordSpacing = value.percent() * fontCascade().spaceWidth() / 100;
1852 break;
1853 case LengthType::Fixed:
1854 fontWordSpacing = value.value();
1855 break;
1856 case LengthType::Calculated:
1857 fontWordSpacing = value.nonNanCalculatedValue(maxValueForCssLength);
1858 break;
1859 default:
1860 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
1861 fontWordSpacing = 0;
1862 break;
1863 }
1864 m_inheritedData.access().fontCascade.setWordSpacing(fontWordSpacing);
1865 m_rareInheritedData.access().wordSpacing = WTFMove(value);
1866}

1884void RenderStyle::setFontSize(float size)
1885{
1886 // size must be specifiedSize if Text Autosizing is enabled, but computedSize if text
1887 // zoom is enabled (if neither is enabled it's irrelevant as they're probably the same).

1897 description.setSpecifiedSize(size);

1901 fontCascade().update(currentFontSelector);
1902}

1944LayoutBoxExtent RenderStyle::shadowExtent(const ShadowData* shadow)
1945{
1946 LayoutUnit top;
1947 LayoutUnit right;
1948 LayoutUnit bottom;
1949 LayoutUnit left;
1950
1951 for ( ; shadow; shadow = shadow->next()) {
1952 if (shadow->style() == ShadowStyle::Inset)
1953 continue;
1954
1955 auto extentAndSpread = shadow->paintingExtent() + shadow->spread();
1956 top = std::min<LayoutUnit>(top, shadow->y() - extentAndSpread);
1957 right = std::max<LayoutUnit>(right, shadow->x() + extentAndSpread);
1958 bottom = std::max<LayoutUnit>(bottom, shadow->y() + extentAndSpread);
1959 left = std::min<LayoutUnit>(left, shadow->x() - extentAndSpread);
1960 }
1961
1962 return { top, right, bottom, left };
1963}
1964
1965LayoutBoxExtent RenderStyle::shadowInsetExtent(const ShadowData* shadow)
1966{
1967 LayoutUnit top;
1968 LayoutUnit right;
1969 LayoutUnit bottom;
1970 LayoutUnit left;
1971
1972 for ( ; shadow; shadow = shadow->next()) {
1973 if (shadow->style() == ShadowStyle::Normal)
1974 continue;
1975
1976 auto extentAndSpread = shadow->paintingExtent() + shadow->spread();
1977 top = std::max<LayoutUnit>(top, shadow->y() + extentAndSpread);
1978 right = std::min<LayoutUnit>(right, shadow->x() - extentAndSpread);
1979 bottom = std::min<LayoutUnit>(bottom, shadow->y() - extentAndSpread);
1980 left = std::max<LayoutUnit>(left, shadow->x() + extentAndSpread);
1981 }
1982
1983 return { top, right, bottom, left };
1984}

1999}

2016Color RenderStyle::unresolvedColorForProperty(CSSPropertyID colorProperty, bool visitedLink) const
2017{
2018 switch (colorProperty) {
2019 case CSSPropertyColor:
2020 return visitedLink ? visitedLinkColor() : color();
2021 case CSSPropertyBackgroundColor:
2022 return visitedLink ? visitedLinkBackgroundColor() : backgroundColor();
2023 case CSSPropertyBorderBottomColor:
2024 return visitedLink ? visitedLinkBorderBottomColor() : borderBottomColor();
2025 case CSSPropertyBorderLeftColor:
2026 return visitedLink ? visitedLinkBorderLeftColor() : borderLeftColor();
2027 case CSSPropertyBorderRightColor:
2028 return visitedLink ? visitedLinkBorderRightColor() : borderRightColor();
2029 case CSSPropertyBorderTopColor:
2030 return visitedLink ? visitedLinkBorderTopColor() : borderTopColor();
2031 case CSSPropertyFill:
2032 return fillPaintColor();
2033 case CSSPropertyFloodColor:
2034 return floodColor();
2035 case CSSPropertyLightingColor:
2036 return lightingColor();
2037 case CSSPropertyOutlineColor:
2038 return visitedLink ? visitedLinkOutlineColor() : outlineColor();
2039 case CSSPropertyStopColor:
2040 return stopColor();
2041 case CSSPropertyStroke:
2042 return strokePaintColor();
2043 case CSSPropertyStrokeColor:
2044 return visitedLink ? visitedLinkStrokeColor() : strokeColor();
2045 case CSSPropertyBorderBlockEndColor:
2046 case CSSPropertyBorderBlockStartColor:
2047 case CSSPropertyBorderInlineEndColor:
2048 case CSSPropertyBorderInlineStartColor:
2049 return unresolvedColorForProperty(CSSProperty::resolveDirectionAwareProperty(colorProperty, direction(), writingMode()));
2050 case CSSPropertyColumnRuleColor:
2051 return visitedLink ? visitedLinkColumnRuleColor() : columnRuleColor();
2052 case CSSPropertyWebkitTextEmphasisColor:
2053 return visitedLink ? visitedLinkTextEmphasisColor() : textEmphasisColor();
2054 case CSSPropertyWebkitTextFillColor:
2055 return visitedLink ? visitedLinkTextFillColor() : textFillColor();
2056 case CSSPropertyWebkitTextStrokeColor:
2057 return visitedLink ? visitedLinkTextStrokeColor() : textStrokeColor();
2058 case CSSPropertyTextDecorationColor:
2059 return visitedLink ? visitedLinkTextDecorationColor() : textDecorationColor();
2060 case CSSPropertyCaretColor:
2061 return visitedLink ? visitedLinkCaretColor() : caretColor();
2062 default:
2063 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
2064 break;
2065 }
2066
2067 return { };
2068}
2069
2070Color RenderStyle::colorResolvingCurrentColor(CSSPropertyID colorProperty, bool visitedLink) const
2071{
2072 auto computeBorderStyle = [&] {
2073 switch (colorProperty) {
2074 case CSSPropertyBorderLeftColor:
2075 return borderLeftStyle();
2076 case CSSPropertyBorderRightColor:
2077 return borderRightStyle();
2078 case CSSPropertyBorderTopColor:
2079 return borderTopStyle();
2080 case CSSPropertyBorderBottomColor:
2081 return borderBottomStyle();
2082 default:
2083 return BorderStyle::None;
2084 }
2085 };
2086
2087 auto result = unresolvedColorForProperty(colorProperty, visitedLink);
2088
2089 if (isCurrentColor(result)) {
2090 if (colorProperty == CSSPropertyTextDecorationColor) {
2091 if (hasPositiveStrokeWidth()) {
2092 // Prefer stroke color if possible but not if it's fully transparent.
2093 auto strokeColor = colorResolvingCurrentColor(effectiveStrokeColorProperty(), visitedLink);
2094 if (strokeColor.isVisible())
2095 return strokeColor;
2096 }
2097
2098 return colorResolvingCurrentColor(CSSPropertyWebkitTextFillColor, visitedLink);
2099 }
2100
2101 auto borderStyle = computeBorderStyle();
2102 if (!visitedLink && (borderStyle == BorderStyle::Inset || borderStyle == BorderStyle::Outset || borderStyle == BorderStyle::Ridge || borderStyle == BorderStyle::Groove))
2103 return SRGBA<uint8_t> { 238, 238, 238 };
2104
2105 return visitedLink ? visitedLinkColor() : color();
2106 }
2107
2108 return result;
2109}
2110
2111Color RenderStyle::colorResolvingCurrentColor(const Color& color) const
2112{
2113 if (isCurrentColor(color))
2114 return this->color();
2115
2116 return color;
2117}
2118
2119Color RenderStyle::visitedDependentColor(CSSPropertyID colorProperty) const
2120{
2121 Color unvisitedColor = colorResolvingCurrentColor(colorProperty, false);
2122 if (insideLink() != InsideLink::InsideVisited)
2123 return unvisitedColor;
2124
2125#if ENABLE(CSS_COMPOSITING)
2126 if (isInSubtreeWithBlendMode())
2127 return unvisitedColor;
2128#endif
2129
2130 Color visitedColor = colorResolvingCurrentColor(colorProperty, true);
2131
2132 // FIXME: Technically someone could explicitly specify the color transparent, but for now we'll just
2133 // assume that if the background color is transparent that it wasn't set. Note that it's weird that
2134 // we're returning unvisited info for a visited link, but given our restriction that the alpha values
2135 // have to match, it makes more sense to return the unvisited background color if specified than it
2136 // does to return black. This behavior matches what Firefox 4 does as well.
2137 if (colorProperty == CSSPropertyBackgroundColor && visitedColor == Color::transparentBlack)
2138 return unvisitedColor;
2139
2140 // Take the alpha from the unvisited color, but get the RGB values from the visited color.
2141 return visitedColor.colorWithAlpha(unvisitedColor.alphaAsFloat());
2142}

2144Color RenderStyle::visitedDependentColorWithColorFilter(CSSPropertyID colorProperty) const
2145{
2146 if (!hasAppleColorFilter())
2147 return visitedDependentColor(colorProperty);
2148
2149 return colorByApplyingColorFilter(visitedDependentColor(colorProperty));
2150}

2379void RenderStyle::setColumnStylesFromPaginationMode(const Pagination::Mode& paginationMode)
2380{
2381 if (paginationMode == Pagination::Unpaginated)
2382 return;
2383
2384 setColumnFill(ColumnFill::Auto);
2385
2386 switch (paginationMode) {
2387 case Pagination::LeftToRightPaginated:
2388 setColumnAxis(ColumnAxis::Horizontal);
2389 if (isHorizontalWritingMode())
2390 setColumnProgression(isLeftToRightDirection() ? ColumnProgression::Normal : ColumnProgression::Reverse);
2391 else
2392 setColumnProgression(isFlippedBlocksWritingMode() ? ColumnProgression::Reverse : ColumnProgression::Normal);
2393 break;
2394 case Pagination::RightToLeftPaginated:
2395 setColumnAxis(ColumnAxis::Horizontal);
2396 if (isHorizontalWritingMode())
2397 setColumnProgression(isLeftToRightDirection() ? ColumnProgression::Reverse : ColumnProgression::Normal);
2398 else
2399 setColumnProgression(isFlippedBlocksWritingMode() ? ColumnProgression::Normal : ColumnProgression::Reverse);
2400 break;
2401 case Pagination::TopToBottomPaginated:
2402 setColumnAxis(ColumnAxis::Vertical);
2403 if (isHorizontalWritingMode())
2404 setColumnProgression(isFlippedBlocksWritingMode() ? ColumnProgression::Reverse : ColumnProgression::Normal);
2405 else
2406 setColumnProgression(isLeftToRightDirection() ? ColumnProgression::Normal : ColumnProgression::Reverse);
2407 break;
2408 case Pagination::BottomToTopPaginated:
2409 setColumnAxis(ColumnAxis::Vertical);
2410 if (isHorizontalWritingMode())
2411 setColumnProgression(isFlippedBlocksWritingMode() ? ColumnProgression::Normal : ColumnProgression::Reverse);
2412 else
2413 setColumnProgression(isLeftToRightDirection() ? ColumnProgression::Reverse : ColumnProgression::Normal);
2414 break;
2415 case Pagination::Unpaginated:
2416 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
2417 break;
2418 }
2419}

2615Vector<PaintType, 3> RenderStyle::paintTypesForPaintOrder(PaintOrder order)
2616{
2617 Vector<PaintType, 3> paintOrder;
2618 switch (order) {
2619 case PaintOrder::Normal:
2620 FALLTHROUGH;
2621 case PaintOrder::Fill:
2622 paintOrder.append(PaintType::Fill);
2623 paintOrder.append(PaintType::Stroke);
2624 paintOrder.append(PaintType::Markers);
2625 break;
2626 case PaintOrder::FillMarkers:
2627 paintOrder.append(PaintType::Fill);
2628 paintOrder.append(PaintType::Markers);
2629 paintOrder.append(PaintType::Stroke);
2630 break;
2631 case PaintOrder::Stroke:
2632 paintOrder.append(PaintType::Stroke);
2633 paintOrder.append(PaintType::Fill);
2634 paintOrder.append(PaintType::Markers);
2635 break;
2636 case PaintOrder::StrokeMarkers:
2637 paintOrder.append(PaintType::Stroke);
2638 paintOrder.append(PaintType::Markers);
2639 paintOrder.append(PaintType::Fill);
2640 break;
2641 case PaintOrder::Markers:
2642 paintOrder.append(PaintType::Markers);
2643 paintOrder.append(PaintType::Fill);
2644 paintOrder.append(PaintType::Stroke);
2645 break;
2646 case PaintOrder::MarkersStroke:
2647 paintOrder.append(PaintType::Markers);
2648 paintOrder.append(PaintType::Stroke);
2649 paintOrder.append(PaintType::Fill);
2650 break;
2651 };
2652 return paintOrder;
2653}

2655float RenderStyle::computedStrokeWidth(const IntSize& viewportSize) const
2656{
2657 // Use the stroke-width and stroke-color value combination only if stroke-color has been explicitly specified.
2658 // Since there will be no visible stroke when stroke-color is not specified (transparent by default), we fall
2659 // back to the legacy Webkit text stroke combination in that case.
2660 if (!hasExplicitlySetStrokeColor())
2661 return textStrokeWidth();
2662
2663 const Length& length = strokeWidth();
2664
2665 if (length.isPercent()) {
2666 // According to the spec, https://drafts.fxtf.org/paint/#stroke-width, the percentage is relative to the scaled viewport size.
2667 // The scaled viewport size is the geometric mean of the viewport width and height.
2668 ExceptionOr<float> result = length.value() * (viewportSize.width() + viewportSize.height()) / 200.0f;
2669 if (result.hasException())
2670 return 0;
2671 return result.releaseReturnValue();
2672 }
2673
2674 if (length.isAuto() || !length.isSpecified())
2675 return 0;
2676
2677 return floatValueForLength(length, viewportSize.width());
2678}
2679
2680bool RenderStyle::hasPositiveStrokeWidth() const
2681{
2682 if (!hasExplicitlySetStrokeWidth())
2683 return textStrokeWidth() > 0;
2684
2685 return strokeWidth().isPositive();
2686}

2693UsedClear RenderStyle::usedClear(const RenderObject& renderer)
2694{
2695 auto computedValue = renderer.style().clear();
2696 switch (computedValue) {
2697 case Clear::None:
2698 return UsedClear::None;
2699 case Clear::Left:
2700 return UsedClear::Left;
2701 case Clear::Right:
2702 return UsedClear::Right;
2703 case Clear::Both:
2704 return UsedClear::Both;
2705 case Clear::InlineStart:
2706 case Clear::InlineEnd:
2707 auto containingBlockDirection = renderer.containingBlock()->style().direction();
2708 if (containingBlockDirection == TextDirection::RTL)
2709 return computedValue == Clear::InlineStart ? UsedClear::Right : UsedClear::Left;
2710 return computedValue == Clear::InlineStart ? UsedClear::Left : UsedClear::Right;
2711 }
2712
2713 RELEASE_ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
2714}
2715
2716UsedFloat RenderStyle::usedFloat(const RenderObject& renderer)
2717{
2718 auto computedValue = renderer.style().floating();
2719 switch (computedValue) {
2720 case Float::None:
2721 return UsedFloat::None;
2722 case Float::Left:
2723 return UsedFloat::Left;
2724 case Float::Right:
2725 return UsedFloat::Right;
2726 case Float::InlineStart:
2727 case Float::InlineEnd:
2728 auto containingBlockDirection = renderer.containingBlock()->style().direction();
2729 if (containingBlockDirection == TextDirection::RTL)
2730 return computedValue == Float::InlineStart ? UsedFloat::Right : UsedFloat::Left;
2731 return computedValue == Float::InlineStart ? UsedFloat::Left : UsedFloat::Right;
2732 }
2733
2734 RELEASE_ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
2735}
